message: Happy New Year from my family to yours.
In speaking with WPBF 25 News today, I discussed that Democrats have a clear goal for the 115th Congress: look for commonality, but pledge to stand our ground and fight for the American people.
On the House floor, my Democratic colleagues and I protested Republicans attempt to silence calls for action on gun violence.

The Republican plan to "repeal and replace" the Affordable Care Act will cause tens of millions of people to lose their health coverage. We can't let this happen. Share how you and your family have benefited from the #ACA in the comments below or at http://bit.ly/D21ACA, so we can remind Republicans what is at stake. #ACAWorks #CoverageMatters

Always an incredible honor to hear from President Obama, especially when speaking about how we must save the Affordable Care Act. As he said today, "there is nothing more noble than fighting for the American people." #ACAWorks #ThanksObama
Did you know that Medicare beneficiaries from my state of Florida save nearly $1,000 on prescription drugs? Republicans want to increase costs & #MakeAmericaSickAgain.

I'm standing with Nancy Pelosi and the Pro-Choice Caucus to raise awareness of what ACA repeal means for women. We will stand our ground and fight for women's access to healthcare -- we will not go back. Watch live: http://dems.gov/live #ProtectOurCare

So thrilled to serve as Co-Chair of the Bipartisan Congressional Women's Caucus! Tonight the gavel was passed to me and my fellow co-chair, Rep Susan Brooks. I look forward to working with my colleagues on finding common ground and advocating issues important to the advancement of women and girls.
Attention District 21: Are you attending the Women's March on Washington on January 21? If so, please let my office know! Contact us at 561-998-9045.

Health care isn’t a game — millions of lives are on the line. We must fight back against threats to the Affordable Care Act.   I'm hosting an event on Sunday, January 15 at 2pm in West Palm Beach in support of the ACA. Will you join me? Contact my office for RSVP information: 561-998-9045.

I am deeply concerned over the bomb threats against Jewish institutions, including at least ten in Florida in less than a week. I commend the ADL, as well as the FBI, Homeland Security and local law enforcement for their swift response. We must all stand strong against these hateful efforts to sow fear and distrust.  http://www.jta.org/2017/01/10/news-opinion/united-states/after-day-of-16-bomb-threats-fbi-to-coordinate-with-jewish-community-in-new-reality

Sunday marked 1,000 days of captivity for 196 Chibok girls, who still remain hidden and subject to unimaginable crimes. I want those girls, those young women, to know that they are our daughters, too. They have not disappeared from our minds or our hearts. We will not give up until they are brought home. #BringBackOurGirls

As Americans honor the legacy of the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. today we remain inspired by his life-long dedication to ending discrimination, empowering communities, and encouraging all to pursue the American Dream. Many across the country will honor him today by participating in service events. Let us continue his efforts to bring peace, equality, and justice to all.

The non-partisan Congressional Budget Office (CBO) reveals that 18 million Americans would lose health insurance coverage in the first year after a repeal of the Affordable Care Act. And premiums for people buying individual non-group coverage would double within 10 years! There's more progress to be made with the ACA, but let's build on what we have instead of throwing consumers and the health care industry into chaos.   https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/wp/2017/01/17/18-million-would-lose-insurance-in-first-year-of-obamacare-repeal-without-replacement-cbo-report-says/?postshare=6661484670045149&tid=ss_tw&utm_term=.bc717fd07e20
District Swearing-In for the 115th Congress

Florida 21: If you've spoken with my office about tickets for the inauguration, make sure to pick them up from my office in the Longworth building. We apologize but we do not have any extra tickets, so please only come by if we've confirmed we are holding a ticket for you!   Also, check out this great guide by the Washington Post about how to get around on Inauguration Day: https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/how-to-get-to--or-around--inauguration-day-festivities/2017/01/14/be3407e8-d294-11e6-945a-76f69a399dd5_story.html?utm_term=.14a4087c5b38
A hallmark of our American democracy is the peaceful transition of power and I will attend today's inauguration in that spirit. Full statement: http://bit.ly/2iFByGo
Thankful for these strong, fierce women who are not only colleagues, but great friends. We stand united to protect our care and we won't back down.

With all due respect to President Trump, as to his inaugural remarks today, I do not share his pessimistic view of America or his bias towards extreme nationalism. We are a nation of opportunity, a country that cherishes diversity and the leader of the free world.  Read my full statement on President Trump's Inaugural Address: http://bit.ly/2jVVS3m

On the 44th anniversary of the Roe v. Wade decision, the Supreme Court decision that recognized legal abortion as a constitutional right for women nationwide, I recommit myself to fight for every woman’s right to healthcare. The women of America are watching and we care very deeply about our country and our rights. We will defend them and ensure all women have equal access to the healthcare they need. #RoevWade
Building a wall while tearing down the Affordable Care Act will not make America great.
Wow, in one of his first acts as President, Donald Trump just took the War on Women to a global level by reinstating the Global Gag Rule. Deadly for women and girls around the world.
The age of coat hanger medicine has returned! It may be a new year, new Congress, new Administration, but Republicans are taking us back to a dangerous past.

As the House prepares to vote on the No Taxpayer Funding for Abortion Act, I again took to the floor to oppose this serious action by Republicans to force unwanted pregnancies and eradicate affordable safe abortion. The women of America are on the march and we will not retreat!

Last night, House Republicans passed the so-called "No Taxpayer Funding for Abortion Act" -- a radical assault on women's health care. For women to thrive in the economic and social opportunities of our nation, we must have the ability to control our own reproductive lives with full access to real health care choices. Republican’s unrelenting efforts to force unwanted pregnancies and eradicate affordable and safe abortion will not save lives.   My full statement: http://frankel.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=537
Women's Healthcare Roundtable
NA

On International #HolocaustMemorialDay, we remember the 6 million Jews murdered during the Holocaust. This serves as both a tribute to the enduring memory of the women, men and children who were killed and as a forceful reminder: never forget, never again.

Attention FL21: President Trump doesn’t want Americans to know they can still #GetCovered under the #ACA. Deadline is January 31; sign up and SHARE to spread the word! #CoverageMatters → https://goo.gl/932hBR
Watching my mother defeat breast cancer has been a source of inspiration for me and today I was proud to join the West Palm Beach Koman Race for the Cure.

Protecting Americans from terrorism is a fundamental duty for Congress and the President. With that said, President Trump’s Executive Order that bans helpless children from fleeing starvation, mutilation and death will not make us any safer. Alarmingly, the President has handed terrorists a recruiting tool by sending the message that Muslims are America's enemy. Lady liberty weeps while ISIS is emboldened. I will stand with like minded colleagues to overturn the President’s inhumane, unconstitutional, and dangerous Executive Order.
In case you missed it, I joined MSNBC last night to talk about President Trump's inhumane Executive Order that bans refugees from entering this country. Lady Liberty weeps while ISIS rejoices.

Honored to hear from H.M. King Abdullah II of Jordan, who met with the House Foreign Affairs Committee this morning to discuss our partnership in the fight against ISIS, stability and security in Middle East, and the plight of refugees.

The Republicans hijacked President Obama’s choice for the Supreme Court and now, sadly, President Trump is bowing to his more extreme supporters. Based on his judicial record, Neil Gorsuch will tip a narrowly divided court in a dangerous direction. This nomination puts serious issues at stake, like a woman’s constitutional right to make her own personal health care choices, getting money out of our politics, and ending political gerrymandering. We need a Supreme Court Justice whose record reflects mainstream values and respect for the fundamental rights of all Americans.

Honored to join with my Democratic and Republican colleagues in a meaningful discussion about preventing sexual violence. We heard gut-wrenching stories from sexual assault survivors – we can and must do more to make sure our schools and communities are safe from predators.

Today I had the distinct honor of hearing from panelists on the danger and devastation caused by the refugee ban. These include Iraqi translators who have risked everything to protect Americans abroad and to whom we owe gratitude and protection. President Trump's ban is a misguided, dangerous hoax. It puts our country at risk and jeopardizes the people we should be protecting.
Standing with a bipartisan group of Congresswomen to raise awareness for #AmericanHeartMonth. It's time we find a way to end heart disease among women. #GoRedWearRed

It’s been seven years – and the Republicans still don’t know how they would replace the Affordable Care Act. And while their obsession with repeal may make for good politics, it poses a serious threat to care for millions of Americans living with pre-existing conditions.

From the Washington Post: “the Trump White House’s version of getting tough on Wall Street is to deregulate it.”   This will hurt our economy and families across the country. Once again, President Trump proves he has no interest in protecting Americans’ bottom line – unless they happen to work on Wall Street.
Replenishing our shorelines protects our jobs, our environment and our property -- proud of last week's bipartisan effort to restore South Florida beaches! http://bit.ly/2jHNd8l

The opioid crisis is ravaging communities and hurting families across this nation. With thousands of sober homes, South Florida is a top destination for addicts seeking recovery. Today I heard from doctors about research and treatment to address this deadly epidemic.

Thanks to the Affordable Care Act, the uninsured rate is at the lowest it has *ever* been, meaning more Americans have access to affordable healthcare. We should be building on this progress, not tearing it down. #FightingForAll
Thank you to the "so called" judges of the #9thCircuit for ruling in favor of American values & against President Trump's hateful, dangerous #MuslimBan.
Roundtable with Local Aviation Leaders

Today I met with local leaders to discuss President Trump's weekend visits to Palm Beach County and the impact its having on our airports and aviation businesses. I will take these concerns from our community to the White House.

Candy is nice, but my DC office knows that #WhatWomenWant on this #ValentinesDay is: equal pay, retirement security, healthcare, paid family leave, equality, and quality child care -- just to name a few!
Happy Valentine's Day from the Democratic women of the House! Proud to work with these incredible leaders as we continue fighting for women & American families.

The evidence is mounting -- it's time we get to the bottom of the relationship between the White House and Russia, which is why I'm calling for a bipartisan, independent investigation. #FollowTheFacts  https://goo.gl/0YWaHP

Earlier today I spoke with Suzanne Boyd of CBS 12 News about Russia's connection to this White House and the need for a bipartisan, independent investigation to get to the bottom of this troubling relationship.

For women to thrive in the economic and social opportunities in our nation, we must have the ability to control our own reproductive lives with full access to  health care choices.   But now, here we go again! Another Republican bill aimed at taking us back to the dark, dangerous days when women were prisoners of their own bodies.

I am deeply alarmed by the rise of anti-Semitic attacks in this country -- such hatred will not be tolerated. I call on the Administration to come up with a comprehensive strategy to combat anti-Semitism and hunt down those who make bomb threats to Jewish Community Centers, desecrate cemeteries and commit other hate crimes.

President Trump is taking us backwards. He promised to protect #LGBT Americans and instead he's ripping away protections from trans students. This is cruel. This is not equality. I will continue to fight to #ProtectTransKids.

Great afternoon spent at the Jewish Federation in Boca Raton learning about the many programs offered here. I will always stand alongside the Jewish community as we defend against hate, intolerance, and violence.
Joint Session Guest
Women in Politics at FAU

I'm thrilled that Sherry Riggs will be my guest tomorrow night at President Trump's first address to Congress. She has an important message to bring to Washington: Without the Affordable Care Act, she would not be alive today. Congress owes it to the millions of folks like Sherry to build on the progress we’ve made, not tear it down.  Learn more about Sherry's story: http://bit.ly/2m3ddve

At tonight’s #JointSession I will wear white in honor of the suffragettes, to stand up to the Republican attempts to roll back the progress we’ve made. Democrats will never stand down in our fight to protect access to affordable health care, reproductive rights, equal pay for equal work, paid sick and family leave, secure retirement futures for all Americans, and so much more. We will not go back! #WomenWearWhite

Sadly, the President baits us with platitudes and then switches to policies and actions that are divisive and dangerous. His calls to repeal the Affordable Care Act, defund Planned Parenthood, and end women's full access to health care choices will not make America great again. Along with Democratic women, I proudly wore suffragette white tonight to send a message that women will not go back from our hard earned gains.
Proud of my fellow women Members for wearing suffragette white at last night's #JointSession - we won't go back!
Why we wore white last night:
Democratic Whip Steny Hoyer set out on a mission today to find out where the House Republicans are keeping their *secret* #ACA repeal bill - no luck so far!
I'm going live with NAWBO for Women's History Month, talking about #SheMeansBusiness

This #WomensHistoryMonth, learn about Elizabeth Cady Stanton and her belief in equality for women. From a young age, Stanton witnessed the misrepresentation of women around her. After attending the World Antislavery Convention in 1840, she drafted the “Declaration of Rights and Sentiments,” which demanded equal rights for women. She was a trailblazer for us all! To learn more, visit: go.usa.gov/cv5k3  #LibraryofCongress

Today I met with Palm Beach County Jewish organizations, local and federal law enforcement, and other faith leaders to discuss the recent increase in anti-Semitic threats and attacks. There should be no room in our society for any type of religious bigotry. This community is united against such hatred.

The health care legislation proposed by House Republicans will make America sick again. It will mean millions of families losing health care coverage and will defund Planned Parenthood, while giving out tax breaks to wealthier Americans. It shortens the life of Medicare, jeopardizing the lives of our seniors.
On a #DayWithoutAWoman, #IFightFor gender equality in the workplace, on campus, and at home. Women deserve a government that treats us with respect!
At 12:30pm, I will join my Democratic colleagues on the steps of the U.S. Capitol for our #DayWithoutAWoman press conference. Watch it LIVE here: bit.ly/2mYNKDK
We're LIVE! #DayWithoutAWoman
We raise our voices to say: women's rights are human rights. When women succeed, the world succeeds! #DayWithoutAWoman

As I told ThinkProgress, "We cannot turn our back for one second. We are really here safeguarding the rights of women and girls and their families and we need to be here to do that." Read more about our action in Congress: #DayWithoutAWoman #IWD2017

It was a packed room today at the House Foreign Affairs Committee hearing on Russia's interference in elections. We need to keep having independent reviews and hearings until we get to the bottom of this. #FollowTheFacts

FACT: Republicans do not know how many people will lose coverage under their #PayMoreForLess health care bill. This is unacceptable. Here are 10 reasons why their bill is concerning for all Americans: http://bit.ly/2lU7tVl  Use the comment section below to tell me how the Republican plan will impact you and your family.

Yesterday, the non-partisan Congressional Budget Office showed that the Republicans' #PayMoreForLess health care bill is a merciless assault on working families. Along with devastating cuts to Medicaid, 24 million Americans will lose their health insurance – all to give billions in tax cuts to the wealthiest Americans and corporations. This bill will hurt seniors, children, the disabled, and hard-working families. It takes us in the wrong direction.

There is no one way to define an "American." My grandfather was born in Austria and he came to this country to escape the pending horrors of the Holocaust. He brought his culture and traditions with him, making our country all the richer for it.  Today I was honored to join the naturalization ceremony of more than 100 people from all corners of the world. Welcome, my fellow Americans!

Throughout his campaign, President Trump claimed he alone would be a true defender of programs like Medicare and Medicaid. He lied.   The health care bill he and Speaker Ryan are pushing wouldn’t just make families #PayMoreForLess health coverage – it would kick 24 million Americans off insurance, make huge cuts to Medicaid, and shorten Medicare’s solvency by three years! https://goo.gl/q8ea44

So impressed with Stefan Wan of Wellington, FL, who placed 10th in a national science competition, the 2017 Regeneron Science Talent Search. The contest recognizes the best scientific minds in American high schools. Stefan won for creating a material that can remove phosphorus from water and recycle it as fertilizer. Congrats, Stefan!  http://wlrn.org/post/wellington-whiz-kid-competes-top-science-talent-search

As a mother of a U.S. Marine, I take very seriously the matters of war and peace. President Trump's proposed budget makes outrageous cuts to the international affairs budget -- cutting the State Department by $11 billion dollars will make us less safe and undermines American diplomacy.
Health Care Hearing

The Republicans are pushing a sick plan to repeal the Affordable Care Act and replace it with Trumpcare -- where the wealthy will get huge tax cuts and the rest of America will pay more for less care.

Today, as a Member of the Foreign Affairs Committee, I met with Iraq's Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi. Since 2014, Iraq has made significant gains against ISIL, recapturing more than 60% of territory. Our partnership with this country is of the utmost importance in the fight to destroy ISIL.

Look forward to joining Vice President Biden and my Democratic colleagues as we fight for affordable health care and defend the progress we've made in the last 7 years under the #ACA. Tune in at 10am: goo.gl/MgBBKs

It’s hard to believe, but it has been 7 years to the day since the Affordable Care Act was signed into law by President Obama. And ever since, its protections and guarantees have brought peace of mind to families nationwide, while improving the quality and lowering the costs of our health care. #ACA7

Tomorrow at 11 a.m. I will host a Facebook LIVE town hall to discuss how the Republicans’ health care repeal bill would hurt women’s health, featuring special guest Cecile Richards, President of Planned Parenthood Action Fund! If you have questions for me or for Cecile Richards about how the repeal bill would affect YOUR ability to access health services, submit your question now in the COMMENTS SECTION BELOW. And tune in to the House Democrats page tomorrow at 11 am ET and ask your question in real time!

Tune in to the House Democrats facebook page at 11:00 AM TODAY to watch a LIVE Facebook town hall I'm hosting with the leaders of the Democratic Women's Working Group and Cecile Richards, President of Planned Parenthood Action Fund! We'll be answering your questions about how the Republicans' repeal bill will hurt women's health - ask us your questions in the comments section in real time!

Hi, everyone -- I'm live from Capitol Hill! Heading out to do a Facebook town hall with Reps Lawrence, Speier and Ruiz, and featuring special guest Cecile Richards, President of Planned Parenthood Action Fund. Tune in!
Here with Cecile Richards of Planned Parenthood! Today is a critical day for women's health -- tune in to our Facebook Live Town Hall happening in FIVE minutes!
We are LIVE! Talking about #Trumpcare's impact on women's health.
Still no update on the "Trump-DON'T-care" legislation. I spoke with Jennifer Vasquez of NBC about what passage of this bill would mean for millions of Floridians. #PayMoreForLess

It's been a busy day here in the Capitol! Spoke with NBC earlier, telling them #Trumpcare should really be called "Trump-DON'T-Care" because this sick bill would kick seniors to the curb and make Americans pay more for less coverage.
Well look at that -- the Republicans have delayed the vote on their sick healthcare bill.
Last night was our first vote on the sick Republican healthcare proposal. My good friend Congressman Adam Schiff and I spoke about our opposition to it! #Trumpcare

The Republican health care bill - which really means NO health care - forces older Americans to pay 5x more, kicks 24 million off insurance, makes everyone pay more for less coverage, and steals from the Medicare Trust Fund. I reject #Trumpcare and will join my Democratic colleagues in voting no today.
Today was a great victory for the American people. The very sick Republican health care proposal, Trumpcare, went down with a thud. Watch my statement here:

I sent a letter to President Trump requesting that he help alleviate the financial burden being shouldered by Palm Beach County, the City of West Palm Beach, and Palm Beach County businesses as a result of his repeated visits to Mar-A-Lago.
Yesterday I met so many diverse voices from our community during the Lake Worth Pride Parade. I won't stop fighting for #LGBTQ equality!
Great time tonight at AIPAC meeting with leaders and constituents, discussing the safety and security of Israel -- our great ally.

With his many visits to Mar-a-Lago, President Trump thinks he can run the State Department from his club. Schmoozer-In-Chief at the expense of real diplomacy that saves lives. Today during a House Committee on Foreign Affairs Democrats briefing, I spoke about why this is immoral: http://bit.ly/2nrnkrG
Women small business owners are working hard every day to support their families - AND to create more jobs for Americans all across the country. We must do more to support our women-owned businesses:

Meeting with my constituents from AIPAC, we discussed the critical US-Israel relationship. Israel is our best friend and greatest ally in the Middle East. Bipartisan support for Israel is crucial, now more than ever. We must seek bipartisanship as it is the most effective way to build the lasting support that Israel needs and deserves.
The White House’s denial of science sends an ominous message to the rest of the world. #DefendScience
In Florida, we know hurricanes. And when hurricanes and other natural disasters strike, communities are ravaged – and so are their budgets.   http://bit.ly/2oyCQS5

Met with members of the Alzheimer's Association today to discuss how we can enhance our partnership at a federal level. Alzheimer's effects everyone in the family, especially caregivers and women -- who account for nearly two-thirds of all seniors living with the disease. #EndALZ

Millions of men and women rely on Planned Parenthood for crucial health services - in fact, PP clinics are the ONLY option for many rural Americans, who otherwise would not have access to care. In honor of #PinkOut day, I met with Planned Parenthood reps and told them #IStandWithPP:
Proud to support my constituent, Lois Pope, and her tireless advocacy to give a voice to our disabled-for-life veterans.
Last night's panel ahead of the VA documentary screening, "The Human Cost of War" -- produced by Palm Beach County's Lois Pope!

This upcoming Tuesday is Equal Pay Day - a day when we recognize the urgent need to eliminate the wage gap between men and women. Leading up to Tuesday, I want to hear YOUR STORIES - have you ever been in a position where you were paid less than your male counterpart for doing the same job? Tell me your stories in the comments below.
Thank you Lynn University for hosting a great panel about civility in today's politics.

This morning I spoke at the opening ceremony of the National Crime Victims' Rights Week, organized by the Palm Beach Victims' Rights Coalition. Every year millions of Americans fall victim to crime through no fault of their own. We must support the victims and those advocates who work tirelessly to help them.

No Americans bravely serving our military should have to face sexual harassment. This Wednesday at 10 AM, tune in to my page to watch the Democratic Women's Working Group hold a hearing on the Marines United scandal to discuss SOLUTIONS!
About to do an interview with Politico about my work fighting for the issues that matter to women and their families...here's a fun preview! Full video on the issues to come next week...

This Wed at 10am, I'm cohosting a hearing on the Marines United scandal with my fellow Democratic Women's Working Group chairs Congresswoman Jackie Speier and Rep. Brenda Lawrence. Tune in to my page on Wednesday to watch the hearing LIVE!

Today is #EqualPayDay - the one day a year when women's wages symbolically catch up to men. In 2017, women on average STILL continue to make only 80 cents to every man's dollar. I'm sick and tired of holding press conferences year after year demanding what is only right - equal pay for ALL people. Women work for the same reason men do: to earn a living and to provide for their families. When they aren't paid fairly, the whole family and our economy suffers. It's time for ALL my colleagues in the House to take real action - pass the Paycheck Fairness Act now to eliminate the wage gap once and for all!
We are LIVE! Talking about Equal Pay Day!

We are your mothers, your sisters, your daughters, and your mothers-in-law! We deserve equal pay for the work we're doing to support our families. We won't back down until our rights are recognized! #equalpayday

Big thanks to Democratic Whip Steny Hoyer for his support for #EqualPay today! Fair pay for ALL individuals is a family issue, and one we MUST fight for - time to pass Congresswoman DeLauro's Paycheck Fairness Act and help eliminate the wage gap once and for all.

Our Marines bravely and courageously serve our nation, and they should be protected from all forms of harassment. The egregious, explicit photo-sharing of female Marines on the private "Marines United" facebook page is absolutely disgusting and unacceptable. Tomorrow, I'll be holding a hearing to hear from those who were targeted, and policy experts who can point to solutions. Tune in to my page at 10 am to watch my hearing live!!   https://www.revealnews.org/blog/hundreds-of-marines-investigated-for-sharing-photos-of-naked-colleagues/

Don't forget to tune here at 10:00 am - I'll be hosting a LIVE hearing on Marines United, a case of unacceptable harassment and exploration of our female servicemembers. We must discuss solutions to make sure ALL our military members, regardless of gender, are protected.

Watch the Democratic Women's Working Group's hearing on the Marines United case - we heard from women Marines who were harassed and exploited online by their fellow comrades. No Marine serving our country should EVER face this kind of abuse, and today's hearing provided a forum for raising awareness and finding solutions. I thank these amazing women for their service, their courage, and their bravery for testifying today.
Marines United hearing - part two:

Jeannette Rankin was sworn in to Congress 100 years ago this month - the first woman to serve. Today, as co-chair of the Bipartisan Congressional Women's Caucus, I'm happy to co-host a special order on the House floor celebrating 100 years of women in Congress!

This morning at 9:30 AM, I'll be holding a media avail in the Capitol with fellow Democratic Women House Members calling on Pres. Trump to retract his statements against Susan Rice, a public servant with decades of foreign policy and diplomacy experience. This is simply another attempt to distract from the investigation into Trump's ties with Russia!

The Democratic women and our allies are standing behind Susan Rice, a dedicated public servant with decades of foreign policy and diplomacy experience. By accusing Ambassador Rice of a crime with absolutely no evidence, Donald Trump is once again going after an accomplished woman in order to distract from the issues we should be talking about - namely the investigation into Trump ties with Russia and the country's interference in our election. We demand Donald Trump rescind his baseless accusations against Ambassador Rice.

President Trump signed a law that will weaken internet privacy for Americans, allowing companies to continue selling our most personal information – including private browser history – without knowledge or consent. We shouldn’t have to give up our privacy when we go online. I join my Democratic colleagues as we fight back to restore Americans’ right to basic privacy on the internet.

Last night I celebrated 100 years of women in Congress by honoring one of my heroes, Bella Abzug. Bella wore many hats - literally AND figuratively: an activist, a feminist, a politician, and a fighter. But first and foremost, Bella was (as she described herself) "a very serious woman" who would not back down on the causes she cared about. In these uncertain political times, we must all follow Bella's lead!

The sexual abuse of young athletes by their coaches, trainers, and doctors - adults they trusted - is outrageous and disgusting. What's more, the fact that USA gymnastics sat on reports of abuse for months before taking action is absolutely unacceptable. That's why I joined w/ my co-chair of the Bipartisan Congressional Women's Caucus, Congresswoman Susan W. Brooks to introduce a bill to help put a stop to abuse and ensure it's never swept under the rug:

The war in Syria is the greatest humanitarian crisis since World War II, killing hundreds of thousands and displacing millions of people. The targeted U.S. airstrikes in response to Assad's brutal chemical attack must be followed by a long-term, comprehensive strategy aimed at protecting innocent civilians. The President should work with our allies, consult with Congress, and adopt a humane policy towards refugees fleeing the unspeakable violence.

As we celebrate Passover, let us remember the struggle for freedom that Jews have experienced throughout the ages, and renew our commitment to fighting the forms of bondage that still exist today. Around the world human trafficking runs rampant, yet hides in the shadows. I will continue fighting to end modern day slavery through legislation, like The Visa Transparency Anti-Trafficking Act. http://frankel.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=476

Our Marines fight to protect our country, and we must offer OUR protection of them as well. Last week, I held a hearing on the Marines United scandal - the non-consensual sharing of explicit photos of our female Marines on social media. I was outraged that so many brave Marines were subject to such egregious sexual harassment and exploitation while serving our country. As the mother of a Marine, I know first-hand the selfless sacrifices of those who put on the uniform. What we heard at the hearing is a threat to the morality, integrity, and sustainability of the institution of our military, and we have much work to do to ensure the safety of ALL our servicemembers.

Proud of Palm Beach County for offering paid family leave; however, we must do more to expand access to paid leave for ALL families, all across Florida and the nation. This is a necessity for our families!

Today is a sad day for the millions of women across the country who rely on clinics that receive Title X funding in order to provide crucial health care services, including preventative care. Far too many of these patients will now no longer be able to  access the health services they need, and I'm appalled that the Trump Administration would put these patients' lives in jeopardy by signing this measure into law.

Last week, I had the honor of participating in a week-long bipartisan fact finding and policy discussions sponsored by the Aspen Institute and focused on threat emanating from North Korea’s nuclear program. The delegation visited the U.S. Naval Base at Yokosuka Japan and the demilitarized zone that separates North and South Korea. We met with Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and South Korean Minister Yun Byung-se as well as parliamentarians from Japan and South Korea. Participants in the discussions included high ranking Japanese and South Korean military officials, scholars and current and former officials from the U.S., China, Japan, and South Korea.  Read my full statement about this trip: http://bit.ly/2oFqxEW

Are you a small business that's interested in learning how to gain access to federal contracts? I'm hosting a workshop with representatives from the Small Business Administration -- RSVP & join us at Palm Beach State College at 9:30 am on Monday, April 24!

How does a protester and an activist become a government official? Are there issues Democratic and Republican women in the House can actually collaborate on? What is a surprising or obscure issue you're working on as chair of the Democratic Women's Working Group?  These are just a few of the questions I answered when I sat down for an interview with Politico's "Women's Rule" - see the video below for my answers!

The results of the referendum in Turkey promise to make the country less democratic, less secular, and more bitterly divided than ever. http://www.cnn.com/2017/04/16/opinions/turkey-election-less-democracy-opinion-ghitis/index.html
From "Chair of the Furniture Committee" to Chair of the Democratic Women's Working Group - hear my story:
Never thought I'd be praising Fox News, but good for them for getting rid of Bill O'Reilly. Took long enough!

Very glad to see that definite steps have been taken to prohibit members of the Navy and Marine Corps from distributing/posting explicit photos of individuals without their consent. The Democratic Women's Working Group recently held a hearing where female service members - whose photos were shared without their consent on the Marines United facebook page - were given a chance to testify. Shame on the Republicans for resurrecting this monstrosity of a health care bill. It guts the crown jewel of the Affordable Care Act: protection for the millions of Americans with a pre-existing condition. These cancer survivors, children with autism, diabetics, and pregnant women—among many others—will pay higher costs or worse, won’t get covered at all.  This bill takes health care away from more than 24 million hard-working Americans while imposing a crushing Age Tax, forcing older Americans to pay premiums five times higher than what others pay. To add insult to injury, it shortens the lifespan of the Medicare Trust Fund, raiding the funds seniors depend on to retire in dignity.   “House Democrats unanimously stood strong against passage. We cannot go back to the days when people got sicker and some died because they could not afford health care treatment. I call on my Senate colleagues to stop this horrendous bill in its tracks.
I voted no on #Trumpcare because it will hurt millions of Americans. Shame on those who voted yes.

Local government and disaster relief organizations will do everything possible to help you through this, but because of the unpredictable nature of this storm your personal preparation is key to your safety. I am in contact with local and federal officials to facilitate communication and assistance in any way possible – before, during and after the storm. Today I spoke with CBS 12 News about the opioid crisis, a “chronic condition” right now across the country and especially here in South Florida. President Trump has become a one-man wrecking ball of the American health care system, taking actions that will cause millions of people to lose affordable access to their medical care. I first met Congresswoman Frederica Wilson in 1998 when she was elected to the Florida State House of Representatives. In fact – we became roommates in Tallahassee during our tenure in the state legislature. She walked in wearing a glittery cowboy hat and with a sense of purpose I’ll never forget. After serving as Minority Whip for four years, she was elected to the Florida State Senate, where she acquired the very appropriate nickname of “Conscience of the Senate.” Before she ran for public office, Freddie was an elementary school teacher, principal and school board member in the Miami-Dade area. She founded 5,000 Role Models of Excellence, a program helping at-risk minority youths prepare for college, vocational school and the military. This is where she met Sgt. La David T. Johnson, growing close to him as he advanced through the mentorship program and entered into military service – a career of bravery and selflessness. Freddie’s integrity, depth of knowledge, and compassion for people is indisputable. She comes from the heart and speaks the truth. For these reasons, and many more, I’m proud to stand with #MyFriendFreddie.  http://www.politico.com/arena/bio/rep_frederica_wilson_.html

Republicans just passed a budget that sells out seniors, children, veterans, and hard-working families to give a windfall of tax cuts to Trump’s billionaire and millionaire cronies. President Trump's opioid announcement is all show no money. Nearly 50,000 Americans died in 2016 from opioid or heroin overdoses and the number of overdose deaths has quadrupled since 2000. The federal public heath emergency fund has just $57,000. Trump's announcement is what we call fake news.

Today at the UN Security Council an important debate is taking place: women’s involvement in peace negotiations on the world stage. Right now, tens of millions of women and girls have been displaced from their homes, and countless more are subject to unspeakable violence. Yet, UN peacekeepers are nearly all male, and most peace agreements make no mention of women— effectively silencing women’s voices and overlooking their rights. Studies show that when women have a seat at the table, the prospect that conflict prevention and resolution will succeed rise significantly. This, in turn, benefits our own national security. I am proud to have voted earlier this month for the Women, Peace and Security Act. Let’s build on this progress at the UN today by voicing our commitment to ensuring women’s equal participation in peacemaking. Their futures depend on it.

Today, the House passed important bipartisan legislation, which now heads to the Senate for passage before then being sent to President Trump’s desk. The PRIVATE Act makes it illegal for military members to share explicit photos of others without consent and was passed as part of the 2018 National Defense Authorization Act. Today’s action tells the female warriors who were violated by the shameful sharing of explicit photos that we stand with them. This legislation protects the privacy of all our military personnel and holds those who violate our trust accountable.

Last week I sent a letter to U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs Secretary Shulkin with recommendations to further improve the new Rapid Appeals Modernization Program. These new procedures aim to provide veterans with the fastest possible resolution to benefit appeals. After the pilot program was launched, my Veterans Advisory Council compiled these suggestions to ensure all veterans understand the new procedures and receive the best possible assistance.
